<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-495-738  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 495 738.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  May 28 1990 v7 n22 p4(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>N.J. PUC issues ultimatum to MCI for LATA access fee. (New JerseyBoard of Public Utilities, MCI Communications Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Messmer, Ellen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The New Jersey Board of Public Utilities orders MCI CommunicationsCorp to either pay an 8.22 cents-per-minute compensation charge toNew Jersey Bell Telephone Co for completing calls within the localaccess and transport area or cease doing business in New Jersey.andO;State regulations governing intra-LATA traffic protect New JerseyBell Telephone from competing with the interexchange carriers withthe compensation charge, a charge that is supposed to compensatethe telephone company for presumed lost traffic.andP;  MCI, refusing tofile a list of intra-LATA services, has avoided paying thecompensation charges.andP;  A petition filed on May 1, 1990 by MCI withthe Board of Public Utilities to lift the compensation charge wasdenied.andP;  The Board agreed to conduct a legal proceeding to examinethe rate of compensation; US Sprint Communications Co and ATandamp;Tvolunteered to join MCI in protesting charges.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (services).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     New Jersey. Board of Public UtilitiesGovernment RegulationCommunications Service SuppliersTelecommunicationsCompetition.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>